\begin_layout Abstract
This paper proposes a novel modeling method for a hybrid quad/triangle mesh
 by enhancing the global object curvature.
 This method uses an adapted extension of the Laplace Beltrami operator.
 Along with the method, this work also presents new applications in sculpting
 and modeling, with subdivision of surfaces and weight vertex groups.
 A series of graphics examples demonstrates the quality, predictability
 and flexibility of the method in a real production environment with software
 blender.
\end_layout

